# Pluralsight
**Category:** ventures
**Domain:** edtech / online learning / tech workforce development
**Website:** https://www.pluralsight.com

## Overview
Pluralsight is an online education platform that offers a library of video courses and skill assessments focused on technology and software development. Founded in 2004, the company provides content covering programming languages, cloud computing, data science, cybersecurity, and other IT disciplines. Its model targets both individual learners and enterprise clients seeking to upskill their technical teams.

The platform’s “skill IQ” and “role IQ” assessments help benchmark learner proficiency and guide personalized learning paths. Pluralsight has grown to serve thousands of businesses and millions of learners worldwide, playing a significant role in closing the technology skills gap. In 2021, the company was acquired by Vista Equity Partners in a take-private transaction.

## Utah connection
Pluralsight was founded and is headquartered in Farmington, Utah, a community within the Salt Lake City metropolitan area. It is a flagship company of Utah’s “Silicon Slopes” tech cluster, with deep roots in the local entrepreneurial and engineering talent pool. The company’s success helped establish Utah as a hub for edtech and software training ventures.

